-- ST Engineering says ex-employees charged with corruption, fraud
-- By Rujun Shen
-- Wed Dec 10, 2014 10:29PM EST
-- None



SINGAPORE, Dec 11 (Reuters) - Singapore Technologies Engineering Ltd <STEG.SI> said on Thursday a local court had charged two former executives with corruption.

A third former executive was also charged with fraud, the company said in a statement. The three executives used to work in the aerospace and marine subsidiaries, the statement added, without giving any further details. [ID:nSNZ11D0yB]